        <body>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 15.9833px; font-family: &amp;quot;AP Letter&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;AP Letter_EmbeddedFont&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;AP Letter_MSFontService&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;AP Letter_MSFontService&amp;quot;, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Customer Needs replaces Guided Qualification and is now editable.​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 15.9833px; font-family: &amp;quot;AP Letter&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;AP Letter_EmbeddedFont&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;AP Letter_MSFontService&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;AP Letter_MSFontService&amp;quot;, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Customer Needs replaces Guided Qualification and is now editable (i.e., you can update the information captured later if it changes).​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;​Select the “Start” button in the “Customer Needs” section to capture the customer needs or &quot;View&quot; to view and edit the single record containing all information about the customer needs, which will be shared across the Lead and the Opportunity records​. Note that the list of “Customer Needs Categories” (previously called “Products &amp;amp; Services”) along with some questions to ask customers have changed.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Also remember to select the &quot;Interested Services&quot; before you qualify the Lead​.&lt;/p&gt;</body>
